title: Software Engineer Intern
description: At PayPal, I contributed to the development of internal tools designed to test developer APIs and new product releases. My primary project involved creating a mock storefront that simulated a consumer-facing interface, allowing developers to edit and test API endpoints effectively.

title: Student Software Developer
description: In the Molecular Evolution Core Lab, I developed web applications for Sanger Sequencing and TipCycle, enhancing systems for client management and technician workflows. My efforts included leading performance optimizations by reducing bundle sizes and eliminating redundant code.

title: Software Engineer Intern
description: At Fyve By, an aviation startup, I worked on both backend and frontend development for a web application managing hangar scheduling and operations. Additionally, I developed an iOS app integrating Unity for 3D hangar simulations and collision detection to assist ground crews.

title: Student Software Developer
description: At the Georgia Institute of Technology's Social Dynamics and Well-Being Lab, I created a web application for an opioid use disorder study. The platform featured analytics tracking, a quiz system, and supported interaction with GPT-4 generated and human-written content.
